name: Custom Narrative Portrait
description:
I enjoy creating  custom paintings that are meaningful and full of metaphor.  My custom Narrative Portraits (weddings,new births,etc.) Family Portraits and Dream Portraits have become cherished mementos passed down through generations.  I will paint an original, one of a kind, custom narrative portrait like the examples at left using  acrylic  12" x 16", or a 14" x 18" panel.  Just email photos of the subjects for reference (I do not copy photos) with any specific desires for the composition.  I will email a rough sketch for your approval and wait for payment to clear before starting the painting. 
 
The piece will be signed and dated,ready to hang (no framing necessary,) carefully packaged and shipped in a hard mailer.

Other sizes/prices available upon request.  Please see other items, for more ideas and examples. I love creating original and meaningful artwork for people, so feel free to contact me with any questions.

name: The Path - Print
description:
© Mari Dieumegard 2011

"If you can see your path laid out in front of you step by step, you know it's not your path. Your own path you make with every step you take. That's why it's your path." 
- Joseph Campbell

Now the question in this particular print is: Are you (the viewer) turning and looking back from where you came and viewing your own path, or are you striding forward with someone else's path in sight?

name: Simple Gifts - Print
description:
© Mari Dieumegard 2010
llustration of a traditional Shaker song of Thanksgiving.

It's a gift to be simple it's a gift to be free
It's a gift to come down where we ought to be.
And when we find ourselves in the place just right,
we will be in the valley of love and delight.

When true simplicity is gained
to bow and to bend we will not be ashamed.
To turn, turn will be our delight
till by turning, turning we come round right.

til I'm flying through the air

~ Ellis Paul
